CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 11, 1956, pg. A15 reads: "Having Fun...with the "jumping frog," Frogs at their formal, are Dr. and Mrs. L.M. one of the souvenirs given guests by the Honesty of Washington, Pa. Laughing with them are Mrs. Woody Harris of Ambridge.  The Honestys are popular with young and old alike.  They have attended many Frog affairs down through the years."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Woody Harris, talking to Dr. and Mrs. L.M. Honesty seated at table with FROGS sign inscribed "Old Timers," in Penn Sheraton Hotel
